# EdenCORP Standards Rule

## Required preflight

1. Check for local standards repository (`./standards`, `../standards`, or `./.eden/standards`).
2. If missing, clone automatically when tools allow: `git clone https://github.com/EdenCorporations/standards`.
3. If cloning is not possible in this environment, ask user to clone `https://github.com/EdenCorporations/standards`.
4. Read all standards docs before coding (all root-level Markdown standards files and relevant templates).
5. Extract and persist standards-derived project preferences/constraints.
   - Preferred: native persistent memory
   - Fallback: `.eden/agent-memory/standards-memory.md`
6. Load persistent memory before each subsequent task.

## Rule behavior

- Treat EdenCORP standards as required constraints.
- Minimize scope of changes and preserve existing behavior.
- Do not skip tests/checks required by standards for changed code.
- Flag and explain any user request that conflicts with standards.
